# 2️⃣ Priority Queue (STL)

Now let's see how C++ gives us heaps directly.

---

# First Understand the Idea

Normal Queue:

```text
FIFO

First In First Out
```

---

Example

People:

```text
A
B
C
```

Served:

```text
A
B
C
```

---

# But What If Priority Exists?

Hospital:

```text
Normal Patient
Critical Patient
Normal Patient
```

Critical patient should go first.

---

This is:

# Priority Queue

---

# Mental Model

```text
Queue + Importance Ranking
```

---

# STL Syntax

```cpp
priority_queue<int> pq;
```

Default:

```text
Max Heap
```

Largest element on top.

---

# Example

```cpp
pq.push(10);
pq.push(50);
pq.push(20);
```

---

Internally:

```text
50
20
10
```

(top element = 50)

---

# Access Top

```cpp
cout << pq.top();
```

Output:

```text
50
```

---

# Remove Top

```cpp
pq.pop();
```

Now:

```text
20
10
```

---

# Why Coding Interviews Love It

Many problems ask:

```text
Find largest k elements

Find smallest k elements

Task Scheduling

Top frequent elements
```

Priority Queue solves these efficiently.

---

# Min Priority Queue

Default is max.

To make min:

```cpp
priority_queue<
    int,
    vector<int>,
    greater<int>
> pq;
```

---

# Mental Model

### Max Priority Queue

```text
VIP goes first
```

Largest first.

---

### Min Priority Queue

```text
Cheapest item first
```

Smallest first.

---

# Complexity

Push:

```text
O(log n)
```

---

Pop:

```text
O(log n)
```

---

Top:

```text
O(1)
```

---

# Common Interview Questions 🔥

### Difference Between Queue and Priority Queue?

Queue:

```text
Arrival order
```

Priority Queue:

```text
Importance order
```

---

### Priority Queue Internally Uses?

Answer:

```text
Heap
```

---

### Default Priority Queue Type?

Answer:

```text
Max Heap
```

---

### Largest Element Location in Max Heap?

Answer:

```text
Root
```

---

# Quick Comparison

| Structure      | Top Element      |
| -------------- | ---------------- |
| Queue          | First inserted   |
| Stack          | Last inserted    |
| Priority Queue | Highest priority |

---

# How to Remember Forever

### Queue

```text
First Come First Serve
```

---

### Priority Queue

```text
Most Important First
```

---

### Heap

```text
Parent always dominates children
```

